{{Quote|Good luck, Luke! See you at the rendezvous.|[[Wedge Antilles/Legends|Wedge Antilles]], addressing [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] shortly before evacuating [[Hoth/Legends|Hoth]]|<ref name="Episode V" />}}
'''Haven''' was the codename of the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance's]] predetermined rendezvous point far beyond the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim Territories]] in the [[Galactic Rim/Legends|Galactic Rim]], where the [[Alliance Fleet/Legends|Alliance Fleet]] regrouped after the Rebellion's defeat at the [[Battle of Hoth/Legends|Battle of Hoth]] in [[3 ABY/Legends|3 ABY]]. The rendezvous point lay near the coordinates 2.427 by 3.886 by 673.52 above the [[The galaxy/Legends|galactic]] plane.

==History==
{{Quote|When you've gotten past the energy shield, proceed directly to the rendezvous point.|[[Princess/Legends|Princess]] [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]], addressing [[Rogue Squadron/Legends|Rogue Squadron]] shortly before the Battle of Hoth|<ref name="Episode V" />}}
[[File:Rebel_fleet_ESB.jpg|thumb|left|250px|The [[Alliance Fleet/Legends|Alliance Fleet]] regroups at Haven]]
During the period of [[2 ABY/Legends|2 ABY]] to [[3 ABY/Legends|3 ABY]], during which the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebellion's]] secret headquarters operated on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Hoth/Legends|Hoth]] at [[Echo Base/Legends|Echo Base]], much of the Rebellion's nerve center, including [[Alliance High Command/Legends|High Command]], was stationed there. Following the [[Battle of Hoth/Legends|Battle of Hoth]], all Alliance personnel were forced to evacuate the planet in the face of [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] assault. Per standard operating procedures, as devised by [[General/Legends|General]] [[Carlist Rieekan/Legends|Carlist Rieekan]], survivors regrouped at the secret rendezvous point, a predetermined location outside [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]] where the Empire could not track them. However, their rendezvous point was nearly [[Skirmish at Haven|exposed]] when an [[Unidentified Strike-class medium cruiser|Imperial]] [[Strike-class medium cruiser|Strike Cruiser]] found them, so the [[Alliance Fleet/Legends|Alliance Fleet]] decided to detour in case the destroyed Strike Cruiser did indeed transmit the coordinates of the [[Fleet/Legends|fleet]] to the Empire.

That point, code-named "Haven" by the Rebels,<ref name="SOL">''[[Shield of Lies]]''</ref> was located beyond the [[Galactic Rim/Legends|Galactic Rim]], far above the galactic equatorial plane and far away from any [[Star/Legends|stars]]. It was beyond the galaxy's [[Gravity well/Legends|gravity well]], making it a perilous journey to reach, one that many of the Rebel [[Starship/Legends|ships]] escaping from Hoth may not have been able to make. It is likely that the Rebellion suffered additional losses in the attempt to reach that point.<ref name="TZ4L" />

[[File:Empire_endshot.png|thumb|right|245px|[[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]], [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]], [[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]] and [[R2-D2/Legends|R2-D2]] watch the [[Millennium Falcon/Legends|''Millennium Falcon'']] depart the rendezvous point]]
During their hunt for the crew of the [[Millennium Falcon/Legends|''Millennium Falcon'']], the [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunters]] [[Zuckuss/Legends|Zuckuss]] and [[4-LOM/Legends|4-LOM]] believed [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] would attempt to reach the rendezvous point considering he carried vital Rebel personnel with him. Through intuitive meditation, Zuckuss determined that the rendezvous point was at the coordinates 2.427 by 3.886 by 673.52 above the galactic plane, a journey of approximately two [[Standard day/Legends|standard days]] from the [[Hoth system/Legends|Hoth system]]. In actuality, the rendezvous point was two degrees off of these coordinates.<ref name="TZ4L" />

There, High Command and a portion of the Rebel fleet, as well as many surviving personnel from Hoth, regrouped to continue their fight against the Empire. The bulk of the fleet, however, was ordered away from Hoth during the Rebels' time there, in accordance with a tactical doctrine devised by [[Gial Ackbar/Legends|Gial Ackbar]], [[Supreme Commander (Alliance)/Legends|Supreme Commander of the Alliance Fleet]]. High Command and the Rebel fleet were to be kept separate from each other in order to avoid being found and wiped out by the [[Imperial Navy/Legends|Imperial Navy]] in one fell swoop. It was determined that the Rebellion could withstand the loss of either High Command or its fleet, but not both.

